                                                    Steelcase Reports First Quarter Results
                                                


                                                    GlobeNewswire – 
                                                    4:10 PM ET 06/21/2017
                                                


Steelcase Inc. (SCS) today reported first quarter revenue of $735.1 million and net income of $18.1 million, or diluted earnings of $0.15 per share. Revenue increased 2 percent, or approximately 4 percent on an organic basis, in the first quarter compared to the prior year, while orders increased 1 percent. Our first quarter results were consistent with our expectations.

















                                                    Steelcase Recognized as One of the Most Civic-Minded Companies in the U.S. for a Second Year
                                                


                                                    GlobeNewswire – 
                                                    9:03 AM ET 06/21/2017
                                                


Steelcase (SCS) was recognized today as one of the most community-minded companies in the nation as a part of the Civic 50, an initiative of Points of Light. Steelcase (SCS) believes we have an important responsibility to play an active role in our communities, said Deb Bailey, director of global corporate relations at Steelcase.

















                                                    Steelcase and Microsoft Showcase Technology-Enabled Spaces Designed to Boost Creative Work at NeoCon 2017
                                                


                                                    GlobeNewswire – 
                                                    11:02 AM ET 06/13/2017
                                                


Steelcase (SCS) today announced it won the 22nd annual IIDA/Contract Magazine Showroom and Booth Design Competition for large showrooms at NeoCon 2017. Steelcase (SCS) and Microsoft bring their respective expertise together to develop holistic spaces specifically designed to optimize Microsoft Surface device technology and support diverse stages and work modes within the creative process.

















